    "5920992": {
      "title": "Polycythemia vera: myths, mechanisms, and management",
      "abstract": "Polycythemia vera is a clonal disorder arising in a multipotent hematopoietic progenitor cell that causes the accumulation of morphologically normal red cells, white cells, platelets, and their progenitors in the absence of a definable stimulus and to the exclusion of nonclonal hematopoiesis.[1][1"
